{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a4aac89b1c1b7db5a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Deep WEB research (WebSearch + WebFetch; cite URLs throughout). Do not answer from memory alone. Question: what does it actually take for an AI system to BUILD/IMPROVE ITS OWN CODE autonomously (\"recursive self-improvement\", true autonomic evolution)?\n\nResearch the real systems and their mechanisms, results, and LIMITS:\n1. **Darwin Gödel Machine** (Sakana AI, 2025) — how it self-modifies its own code, the empirical-vs-provable shift from Schmidhuber's Gödel Machine, results on SWE-bench/Polyglot, and its stated limitations/safety notes.\n2. **AlphaEvolve** (DeepMind, 2025) — evolutionary coding with an LLM + automated evaluators; what it can and cannot do; the role of the verifier/eval function.\n3. **STOP** (Self-Taught Optimizer), **SICA** (Self-Improving Coding Agent), **ADAS** (Automated Design of Agentic Systems), **Voyager** — the spectrum from improving prompts/scaffolds to rewriting the agent's own code. What level of self-modification each actually achieves.\n4. **The verifier/seed requirement**: every working self-improver needs a ground-truth evaluator (tests/benchmark) and a capable enough base model to write code that compiles + passes. What is the consensus on the \"you can't bootstrap above your verifier / base capability\" limit? Reward hacking / objective-gaming in self-improving loops.\n5. **Safety of self-modifying CODE** (not just prompts): the risks of letting a system edit its own execution kernel; sandboxing/isolation, capability confinement, the alignment concerns with RSI; any frameworks for bounding it.\n\nEND WITH: (a) a crisp taxonomy of \"levels\" of self-improvement (prompt/skill → scaffold/agent-design → own-source-code → weights), with which are demonstrated vs aspirational; (b) the minimal ingredients a system needs to genuinely self-author code; (c) the honest current ceiling. Cite URLs throughout. Return findings only; do not edit files."},"uuid":"1c8ef724-45f9-48e2-8da1-0f1fc983531e","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:33:36.850Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
