{"parentUuid":"45311857-f156-4938-9896-e9baac50ce26","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a4aac89b1c1b7db5a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the \"deep-research\" workflow.\n\nDeep research harness — fan-out web searches, fetch sources, adversarially verify claims, synthesize a cited report.\n\nWhen the user wants a deep, multi-source, fact-checked research report on any topic. BEFORE invoking, check if the question is specific enough to research directly — if underspecified (e.g., \"what car to buy\" without budget/use-case/region), ask 2-3 clarifying questions to narrow scope. Then pass the refined question as args, weaving the answers in.\n\nPhases:\n- Scope: Decompose question (from args) into 5 search angles\n- Search: 5 parallel WebSearch agents, one per angle\n- Fetch: URL-dedup, fetch top 15 sources, extract falsifiable claims\n- Verify: 3-vote adversarial verification per claim (need 2/3 refutes to kill)\n- Synthesize: Merge semantic dupes, rank by confidence, cite sources\n\nInvoke: Workflow({ name: \"deep-research\", args: \"What does it actually take for an AI system to BUILD/IMPROVE ITS OWN CODE autonomously (recursive self-improvement, autonomic evolution)? Cover: (1) Darwin Godel Machine (Sakana, 2025) self-modification mechanism, empirical-vs-provable shift from Schmidhuber, SWE-bench/Polyglot results, limitations/safety; (2) AlphaEvolve (DeepMind 2025) evolutionary coding + automated evaluators, capabilities/limits, verifier role; (3) STOP, SICA, ADAS, Voyager — spectrum from prompts/scaffolds to rewriting own code; (4) the verifier/seed requirement and the \\\"can't bootstrap above your verifier/base capability\\\" limit, reward hacking; (5) safety of self-modifying CODE — sandboxing, capability confinement, alignment, bounding frameworks. End with: taxonomy of self-improvement levels (demonstrated vs aspirational), minimal ingredients to self-author code, honest current ceiling.\" })"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"32dc4d7f-7bb9-4c2a-bf11-3c294d98cffa","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:33:45.058Z","sourceToolUseID":"toolu_01Tmn8gzDoYJ3o1og5hgqMnD","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
