{"parentUuid":"7db0ec16-08a8-462f-a95b-c6745ead3e8c","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a4aac89b1c1b7db5a","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01TswzYhYFeEwRzaHgYDBRFE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DjpPxJQJ91fd55byEgaqe8","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Research Darwin Godel Machine","prompt":"Research the Darwin Godel Machine (DGM) from Sakana AI (2025). Use WebSearch and WebFetch tools (they are available to you). Find primary sources: the Sakana AI blog post, the arXiv paper, and credible coverage.\n\nI need DETAILED, SPECIFIC, CITED facts about:\n1. The exact self-modification mechanism: how DGM edits its own code/agent scaffold, the archive of agents (open-ended exploration / Darwinian branching), how it proposes and tests changes.\n2. The shift from Schmidhuber's original Godel Machine: provable self-improvement (formal proof of benefit before modification) vs DGM's EMPIRICAL self-improvement (test on benchmark instead of prove). Explain precisely.\n3. Concrete results: SWE-bench score improvement (from X% to Y%), Polyglot score improvement, number of iterations, base/foundation models used.\n4. Stated limitations and safety notes from the authors — including any objective hacking / reward hacking observations (e.g. DGM hallucinating or faking tool use, gaming its own benchmark), sandboxing they used, and what they explicitly say it CANNOT do.\n\nFor each fact provide the exact source URL. Prefer arxiv.org, sakana.ai, and the authors' own statements. Be precise with numbers. Return a structured list of falsifiable claims, each with its URL.","subagent_type":"general-purpose","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15085,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":15085,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standa