nly works on problems with a machine-gradable/automatically-verifiable objective function. Explain why this is a fundamental constraint and what classes of problems it excludes (e.g. things you can't auto-evaluate).\n3. Concrete results/achievements: the 4x4 complex matrix multiplication improvement over Strassen (48 vs 49 multiplications), the 0.7% recovery of Google datacenter compute (Borg), TPU circuit/arithmetic improvements, Gemini training kernel speedups, advances on open math problems (e.g. ~50 problems, kissing number in 11 dimensions). Give specific numbers with sources.\n4. What AlphaEvolve CANNOT do — stated limits: it does not improve its own LLMs/weights; it requires a verifier; not applicable to problems lacking automated evaluation. Quote DeepMind's own caveats.\n\nFor each fact provide the exact source URL. Prefer deepmind.google, arxiv, and the white paper. Return a structured list of falsifiable claims each with its URL.","outputFile":"/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-gg-Work-Yogi/8c297f37-26ee-4ab6-9c6c-7ec95dbfe2e1/tasks/aa47f8eb58a90b448.output","canReadOutputFile":true},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4f4138d4-ab77-42a5-bdc3-3a040d090e19","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
